PCKISSSS-
P: Process-See the process, NOT the product
C: Curiosity-What is it? How is it made? What can I steal from it?
KI: Kindness- Be kind to others
S: Stupid: Willing to be
S: Steal:  like an artist
S: Stamina: Creative work requires a lot of energy; do not waste it.
S: Smarter than me:  stay with them


GIGO = Garbage IN Garbage OUT

------



Here is my personal roadmap how I implement these frameworks into my daily life as a Senior IT and Infrastructure Analyst and financial risk blogger. 
This maps directly to my background in IT infrastructure, web development, and technical risk auditing.

---

## Implementing PCKISSSS Daily

### P & C: Process & Curiosity

 Daily Action: When analyzing a new financial exploit or a banking system vulnerability, I look past the news headline (the product) and reverse-engineer the breakdown (the process).
 
 Real-Life Example: Instead of just reading about a recent decentralized finance (DeFi) hack, I pull the smart contract data. 
 I ask myself: How did the code allow this? What infrastructure loophole can I expose to protect American self-directed investors?


### KI & S: Kindness & Willing to be Stupid

 Daily Action: I use my 11+ years of banking experience to simplify complex tech jargon for non-tech wealth protectors without being patronizing. 
 I stay willing to ask basic questions during IT infrastructure audits.

 Real-Life Example: When reviewing a bank’s disaster recovery plan, I ask the "stupid" question: What happens if the backup generator fails during a localized power grid failure? 
 Then, I use kindness to translate that risk into a simple, jargon-free blog post for everyday Americans.


### S & S: Steal Like an Artist & Stamina
 Daily Action: I study mainstream financial publications (like Bloomberg or Wall Street Journal) to see what topics trend, but I strip away their dense walls of text. 
 I protect my mental stamina by writing in highly structured, mobile-first sprints.

 Real-Life Example: I find a dense 50-page Federal Reserve report on digital asset risks. 
 I "steal" the core data points, but format them into ultra-concise, 2-sentence paragraphs that are easy to read on a smartphone screen while commuting.



### S: Stay with People Smarter Than Me

 Daily Action: I actively engage with top-tier cybersecurity experts, economic sovereign skeptics, and veteran cloud architects on platforms like LinkedIn or GitHub.
 
 Real-Life Example: I join a specialized forum or thread on banking infrastructure security. 
 I spend 15 minutes a day reading discussions by engineers who are building the next generation of hardware security modules (HSMs).

---

## Implementing GIGO Daily

As an IT analyst, I know that bad data destroys systems. As a writer, I know bad data destroys my credibility.

 Daily Action: I never use unverified data, rumors, or vague AI-generated claims in my risk audits or blog posts. 
 If my input data isn't verified, my final article will be generic fluff.
 
 Real-Life Example: When writing a blog post about U.S. wealth protection, I do not rely on second-hand blog commentary. 
 I go straight to the source—like the FDIC database or IRS tax codes—and verify the numbers before publication.

Here is a quick look at how GIGO impacts my specific content creation workflow:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Input (Garbage In)                                                        | System / Action                                          | Output (Garbage Out) |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Pulling numbers from unverified social media threads or generic AI prose. | Writing a mobile-first blog post on USWealthTech.com.    | High bounce rates, loss of reader trust, and poor SEO ranking.            |
| Using verified mainstream news and official financial statistics.       | Filtering data through my 11+ years of IT and banking expertise. | A highly credible, high-ranking risk audit that empowers sovereign investors. |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

By applying these daily, I ensure my technical analysis stays sharp, my content remains highly readable on mobile devices, and my platform continues to simplify financial sovereignty.


